cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with semantic similarity algorithms and natural language processing techniques to analyze course descriptions and learning objectives. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the use of corpus statistics to improve the accuracy of the semantic similarity algorithm. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper mentions the use of supervised learning data for the algorithm. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with the development of algorithms to analyze and compare learning objectives. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but it could be relevant as the paper discusses the development of tools to improve the transferability of courses between institutions, which could have implications for education policy and society as a whole.
